LORE rakuen-merchant
FLAGS RAKUEN MERCHANT
Garden Ledger controls surplus allocation; check with a Ledger Clerk before
purchasing bulk goods — some commodities are rationed; selling rationed goods
outside the Ledger system is a civil offense
Supply sources: Kowloon sends grain; Kiess sends clerks; Midgaard sends
subsidies but not recognition; this shapes availability and pricing
Common orchards and waterworks are communally maintained; purchasing exclusive
access is a serious social offense regardless of payment offered
Bloom Council rotating stewardship: titles rotate but "stewardship advisors"
who never rotate hold actual permits and institutional bottlenecks
No formal Midgaard trade treaty (three refused petitions); Kowloon and Mafdet
relationships are the growth routes
Abundance-sharing expectations: customers expect community pricing;
charging market rates requires justification in a way it doesn't elsewhere
~
